        <div style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:.6rem;color:var(--purple);letter-spacing:.1em;margin-bottom:.4rem">SURPRISE FINDING</div>
        <div style="font-size:.88rem;line-height:1.65;color:var(--text2)"><strong style="color:var(--text)">23-27 age group argues worst</strong> (2.66/5.0). Lower than both 18-22 and 28+. Early-career overconfidence — arguing from identity, not evidence.</div>
      </div>
      <div style="background:var(--surface);border:1px solid var(--border2);border-radius:14px;padding:1rem">
        <div style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:.6rem;color:var(--amber,#d35400);letter-spacing:.1em;margin-bottom:.4rem">STRONG ARG PATTERN</div>
        <div style="font-size:.88rem;line-height:1.65;color:var(--text2)"><strong style="color:var(--text)">Every strong argument</strong> (score ≥4.0) had the same 3 elements: nuanced position + one data point + counterargument acknowledged. Zero exceptions across 150 arguments.</div>
